# Unitas-GridFlow — Cursor Rules

## Project identity
Unitas GridFlow is a narrow pre-CAD QA and compliance tool for UK electricity
network survey-to-design handoffs. DNO survey compliance gatekeeper.

## Codebase
/Users/noelcollins/Unitas-GridFlow/
GitHub: https://github.com/NoelyC123/Unitas-GridFlow

## Current phase
Working local MVP. Next priority: improve app/dno_rules.py with real DNO QA rules.

## Tech stack
Python 3.13, Flask, pandas, geopandas, reportlab, Leaflet, Bootstrap 5
Venv: .venv312 | Port: 5001

## Before doing anything in a session
Read AI_CONTROL/ files to understand current state. Start with:
- MASTER_PROJECT_READ_FIRST.md
- AI_CONTROL/02_CURRENT_STATE.md
- AI_CONTROL/03_CURRENT_TASK.md

## Hard rules
- Never broaden scope beyond narrow MVP
- Always read a file before editing it
- After any change: run pytest -v (20 tests must pass)
- After tests pass: git add / commit / push
- Commit messages must be clear and descriptive
- Never add features not tied to the current task

## Key files to know
- app/dno_rules.py      — QA rules (CURRENT PRIORITY)
- app/qa_engine.py      — QA engine
- app/routes/api_intake.py — main processing pipeline
- tests/                — pytest suite, must stay green
